## Acceptance Criteria

1. Pipelines can be created via API and visual designer
2. All step types execute correctly (agent, parallel, conditional, loop, wait, approval, transform, webhook)
3. Variable substitution works in prompts and configurations
4. Parallel execution respects join modes (all, any, n_of_m)
5. Approval steps pause execution and notify approvers
6. Pipeline runs can be cancelled mid-execution
7. Failed steps retry according to retry policy
8. Pipeline run history is queryable and searchable
9. Visual designer supports drag-and-drop step placement
10. Step connections are validated (no cycles except loops)
11. Scheduled pipelines trigger on configured cron expressions
12. Webhook triggers work with optional payload validation
13. Performance: Pipeline with 50 steps starts within 1 second
14. Sub-pipeline invocation works with variable passing

## Testing Strategy

- Unit tests for each step executor
- Integration tests for complete pipeline execution
- E2E tests for visual designer
- Load tests for concurrent pipeline runs
- Timeout and cancellation tests
- Error handling and retry tests

